'''[https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/918fzoufe1esbn3d8ce6r/ANsB73aqjHGDkZar1a4vaqM?rlkey=73o1yetzumdq32bt40zllhbb8&e=1&st=kdpsr6cv&dl=0 เอกสารแจ้ง] Loei''' ([[Thai alphabet|Thai]]: [[wikt:เลย|เลย]], {{IPA|th|lɤ̄ːj|pron}}), is one of the more sparsely populated [[Provinces of Thailand|provinces]] (''changwat'') of [[Thailand]]. It lies in the [[Isan]] region of [[Isan#Administrative divisions|upper northeastern Thailand]]. Neighboring provinces are (from east clockwise) [[Nong Khai province|Nong Khai]], [[Udon Thani province|Udon Thani]], [[Nong Bua Lamphu province|Nong Bua Lamphu]], [[Khon Kaen province|Khon Kaen]], [[Phetchabun province|Phetchabun]], and [[Phitsanulok province|Phitsanulok]]. In the north it borders [[Xaignabouli province|Xaignabouli]] and [[Vientiane province]] of [[Laos]].

{{asof|2020}}, the provincial governor is Chaiwat Chuenkosum.<ref>{{cite news |title=Loei governor rises as 'savior' in Covid-19 struggle |url=https://www.thaipbsworld.com/loei-governor-rises-as-savior-in-covid-19-struggle/ |access-date=2 May 2020 |work=Thai PBS World |date=2 May 2020}}</ref> The province was allocated 225.6 million [[Thai baht|baht]] in the [[Fiscal year|FY2019]] Thailand budget.<ref>{{cite book|title=Thailand's Budget in Brief Fiscal Year 2019 |url=http://www.bb.go.th/en/topic-detail.php?id=8562&mid=456&catID=0 |publisher=Bureau of the Budget| page=95|date=20 December 2018|access-date=2 May 2020 }}</ref>
